<paragraph blockId="10.[151,477,151,211]" box="[151,420,186,211]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">(Figs. 15, 30, 45,60–66)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="587" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Yellow. Area near ocelli and below anterior margin of pronotum golden yellow, compound eyes offwhite. Forewing pale yellow, costal margin with anterior, oblique and two posterior, transverse, black fasciae; second apical cell with black spot (Figs. 15, 30 &amp; 45).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
Head angularly produced. Anteclypeus not exceeding facial margin (
<figureCitation box="[990,1077,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 45" captionStartId="4.[157,270,1416,1439]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,212,1389]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1395]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 45. Head &amp; pronotum Sophonia species 31. S. bakeri Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 32. S. bifida Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 33. S. chandrai Meshram &amp; Ramamurthy; 34. S. complexa Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 35. S. complicata Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 36. S. illuminata (Distant); 37. S. insignis Distant 38. S. intricata sp. nov.; 39. S. keralica Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 40. S. linealis (Distant); 41. S. longicephala (Ahmed &amp; Mahmood); 42. S. longitudinalis (Distant); 43. S. modesta (Distant); 44. S. tridenta sp. nov.; 45. S. vidarvya sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400215/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). Ocelli near lateral margins of vertex, distance between eye and ocellus 
<date box="[649,676,403,427]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">3x</date>
diameter of ocellus. Vertex broadly concave and with irregular sculpturing anteriorly. Scutellum 0.8x as long as pronotum. Pronotum 0.65x longer than broad and 0.8X longer than vertex (
<figureCitation box="[291,376,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 45" captionStartId="4.[157,270,1416,1439]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,212,1389]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1395]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 45. Head &amp; pronotum Sophonia species 31. S. bakeri Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 32. S. bifida Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 33. S. chandrai Meshram &amp; Ramamurthy; 34. S. complexa Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 35. S. complicata Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 36. S. illuminata (Distant); 37. S. insignis Distant 38. S. intricata sp. nov.; 39. S. keralica Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 40. S. linealis (Distant); 41. S. longicephala (Ahmed &amp; Mahmood); 42. S. longitudinalis (Distant); 43. S. modesta (Distant); 44. S. tridenta sp. nov.; 45. S. vidarvya sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400215/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
Male genitalia. Pygofer with several macrosetae in posterior half, with caudodorsal angle roundly produced, below which long, slender process arises, directed caudally, upcurved at right angle at midlength, apex slightly hooked, with spinelike branch at base (
<figureCitation box="[595,723,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[198,1338,764,1962]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1355,757,1967]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Male Sophonia vidarvya sp. nov. 60. Male genitalia; 61. Pygofer process; 62. Style; 63. Connective; 64, 65. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 66. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400218/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Fig. 60–61</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate broader medially than at apex and base with median row of six stout macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[574,660,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[198,1338,764,1962]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1355,757,1967]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Male Sophonia vidarvya sp. nov. 60. Male genitalia; 61. Pygofer process; 62. Style; 63. Connective; 64, 65. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 66. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400218/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
). Style slender, preapical lobe robust, apophysis slender, apex short, beaklike (
<figureCitation box="[261,345,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[198,1338,764,1962]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1355,757,1967]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Male Sophonia vidarvya sp. nov. 60. Male genitalia; 61. Pygofer process; 62. Style; 63. Connective; 64, 65. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 66. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400218/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped with stem 2.3x as long as arms, apex expanded (
<figureCitation box="[1148,1231,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[198,1338,764,1962]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1355,757,1967]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Male Sophonia vidarvya sp. nov. 60. Male genitalia; 61. Pygofer process; 62. Style; 63. Connective; 64, 65. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 66. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400218/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus dorsal apodomes with two arms well separated, winglike in middle, each arm with dorsomedianprocesses curved caudally, caudal processdirected anteriorly and in contact with dorsomedian process, caudoventral processes crossing midline caudad of shaft;shaft strongly curved anteriorly, apex flared with two dorsally directed recurved processes (
<figureCitation box="[273,412,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[198,1338,764,1962]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1355,757,1967]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Male Sophonia vidarvya sp. nov. 60. Male genitalia; 61. Pygofer process; 62. Style; 63. Connective; 64, 65. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 66. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400218/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Figs. 64–65</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1147]" box="[199,1430,834,859]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,834,859]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Measurements.</emphasis>
