<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="587" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,942,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name (Sanskrit: 
<taxonomicName box="[671,769,942,966]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vidarvya">
<emphasis box="[671,769,942,966]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">vidarvya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning hoodless) alludes to the aedeagal shaft lacking a hoodlike expansion anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="587" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1014,1039]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[322,533,1014,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vidarvya" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,533,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Sophonia vidarvya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[540,629,1014,1039]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[540,629,1014,1039]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath &amp; Wesley" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Wesley" box="[755,1171,1014,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[755,908,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">S. complicata</emphasis>
Viraktamath &amp; Wesley
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 5, 20, &amp; 35), but can be distinguished by the shape of the aedeagus (features of 
<taxonomicName box="[847,1000,1051,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[847,1000,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">S. complicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parentheses): shaft apex with lateral processes acuminate in posterior view, curved strongly ventrad in lateral view (shaft apical processes rounded in posterior view, straight in lateral view).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
